               <p>JOHN WATSON. I am a <rs id="t18250915-246-viclabel1320" type="occupation">stone-mason</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-246-victim1259 t18250915-246-viclabel1320"></join>. I was in <placeName id="t18250915-246-crimeloc1321">High-street, St. Giles's</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-246-crimeloc1321" type="placeName" value="High-street, St. Giles's"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-246-crimeloc1321" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-246-off1318 t18250915-246-crimeloc1321"></join>, about half-past eight o'clock in the evening, of the 31st of July, and lost my handkerchief, but I did not feel it taken; the officer came, and asked if I had lost it? I said, I had. I did not see the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-246-person1260">
                  JOHN 
                  WOODWARD
               <interp inst="t18250915-246-person1260" type="surname" value="WOODWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-246-person1260" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-246-person1260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was in St. Giles's, and saw the prisoner, and watched him for some time; he and another boy were following Mr. Watson. I crossed over, and saw him trying to put something about him; I took hold of him, and he dropped the handkerchief at his feet.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going on an errand, and saw two boys drop something. I went across the road, and picked it up.</p>

               <p>
